    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n`:restart` works with `:confirm` to ask user configuration if buffers have been modified. However, it does not respect 'confirm'. That makes sense bc restart uses `qall!` by default, but I feel like respecting 'confirm' is expected.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean -u NONE +'set confirm'`\n2. Modify buffer\n3. `:restart`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRestart respects 'confirm' option.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1149+g3f80e18a80-dirty",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
